HEADWORD: Podura
<hw>Po*du"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> L.
<plw>Podur⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>Poduras</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.; Gr. <grk>poy`s</grk>, <grk>podo`s</grk>,
foot + <?/ tail.]</ety> <def>Any small leaping thysanurous insect of the
genus <gen>Podura</gen> and related genera; a springtail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Podura scale</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>one of the
minute scales with which the body of a podura is covered. They are used
as test objects for the microscope.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

